t is higher  and their dedication to make sure their children receive the best is something that unresponsive public schools just cannot meet under todays circumstances.  Less trying to save the world and more getting down to learning is what public schools need.    Last and more importantly, people who send their children to public schools do make a contribution and hence investment in public education by paying their property and other taxes. They just don't have to put up with the nonsense and petty policies of the local public school system. Given this the author is clearly wrong and those parents who send their children to private schools are not foul but merely looking at out for the better interests of their children. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1042" language="en" documentId="4086" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="SNeb" date="Aug 29, 2013 5:52PM" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://living.msn.com/family-parenting/the-family-room-blog-post?post=ab228ffc-1e99-4b37-a7b8-0b6a4c3fb240" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="10" thumbsDown="0" origId="4086" notes="" title="Is it wrong to send kids to private school?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1042"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>